"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-2030444-Olympics-Tom-Ford-Cambridge-Oxford-Boat-Race\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  An ongoing row over criteria eligibility has meant thatOlympicgold medallist Tom Ford has become the fourth rower to be barred from competing for Cambridge at this year's Boat Race.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 183, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 79, \"end\": 87, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Ford\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.89232240377222e-18, \"text\": \"Tom Ford\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Ford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Ford\"}, {\"begin\": 148, \"end\": 157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\", \"score\": 0.9989919692558076, \"rank\": 0.0010090478365564585, \"text\": \"Cambridge\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ford recently began an MBA at the University of Cambridge.\", \"from\": 184, \"to\": 242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 184, \"end\": 188, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ford_Motor_Company\", \"score\": 0.999966114419987, \"rank\": 1.9245576279917855e-05, \"text\": \"Ford\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ford_Motor_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ford_Motor_Company\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But he enrolled for his undergraduate degree atNewcastleUniversity in 2011.\", \"from\": 244, \"to\": 319, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This means he came into conflict with a rule introduced after doubleOlympicgold winner James Cracknell came out of retirement to participate in the race between Oxford and Cambridge in 2019.\", \"from\": 320, \"to\": 510, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 407, \"end\": 422, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Cracknell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"James Cracknell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Cracknell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Cracknell\"}, {\"begin\": 481, \"end\": 487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Oxford\", \"score\": 0.9999820189343596, \"rank\": 1.798138685009805e-05, \"text\": \"Oxford\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Oxford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Oxford\"}, {\"begin\": 492, \"end\": 501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\", \"score\": 0.9989919692558076, \"rank\": 0.0010090478365564585, \"text\": \"Cambridge\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That year's event saw Cracknell become the oldest competitor and winner of theesteemed race.\", \"from\": 511, \"to\": 603, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 533, \"end\": 542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Cracknell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cracknell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Cracknell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Cracknell\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The fallout from Cracknell's victory with Cambridges saw rowing clubs from both universities agree on a new ruling which ensured that athletes cannot not take part in the race if they started an undergraduate course more than 12 years earlier.\", \"from\": 604, \"to\": 847, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 621, \"end\": 630, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Cracknell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cracknell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Cracknell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Cracknell\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ford may have clinched gold for Team GB in the men's eight at the 2024 Paris Olympics but he will not be seated in the boat this year, despite being part of the preparation races.\", \"from\": 849, \"to\": 1028, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 849, \"end\": 853, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ford_Motor_Company\", \"score\": 0.999966114419987, \"rank\": 1.9245576279917855e-05, \"text\": \"Ford\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ford_Motor_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ford_Motor_Company\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 32-year-old assisted the 'provisional Blue Boat', which is Cambridge's Boat Race crew, to victory against the Netherlands in two races ahead of next month's event.\", \"from\": 1029, \"to\": 1196, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1092, \"end\": 1101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\", \"score\": 0.9989919692558076, \"rank\": 0.0010090478365564585, \"text\": \"Cambridge\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, this is only the latest part of the furore after three post-graduate teacher training students, also rowing for Cambridge, were seen as ineligible less than a month before the two universities compete.\", \"from\": 1198, \"to\": 1408, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1319, \"end\": 1328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\", \"score\": 0.9989919692558076, \"rank\": 0.0010090478365564585, \"text\": \"Cambridge\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Matt Heywood, a former under-23 world champion, Molly Foxell and Kate Cowley have all been disqualified from competing in the men's and women's races on the River Thames in April.\", \"from\": 1409, \"to\": 1588, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1414, \"end\": 1421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Heywood\", \"score\": 0.9999779102463537, \"rank\": 2.20902392572663e-05, \"text\": \"Heywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Heywood\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Heywood\"}, {\"begin\": 1457, \"end\": 1462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Molly_Hayes\", \"score\": 0.9999992701005275, \"rank\": 6.593548137944907e-07, \"text\": \"Molly\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Molly_Hayes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Molly_Hayes\"}, {\"begin\": 1474, \"end\": 1478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\", \"score\": 0.9999675745621341, \"rank\": 3.242644886707587e-05, \"text\": \"Kate\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\"}, {\"begin\": 1479, \"end\": 1485, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plant_Oxford\", \"score\": 0.948226124380057, \"rank\": 0.054600769044743896, \"text\": \"Cowley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plant_Oxford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plant_Oxford\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Following an Oxford objection, an independent interpretation panel stated that the three Cambridge rowers were PGCE students and not studying for degrees and so were ruled out.\", \"from\": 1590, \"to\": 1766, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1603, \"end\": 1609, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Oxford\", \"score\": 0.999982018